# CODEOWNERS.example — copy to .github/CODEOWNERS (or the repo root) in the
# project you installed the harness into, then turn on branch protection with
# "Require review from Code Owners" on your default branch.
#
# This is the ENFORCEMENT layer the local uninstall gate cannot provide: once
# these paths are owned, GitHub blocks any PR that adds/removes/edits them from
# merging until the PM (owner) approves. A developer can still change files in a
# branch, but cannot land the change without approval.
#
# Replace @your-pm with the PM's GitHub handle (or a team like @org/governance).

/.harness/**   @your-pm
/.claude/**    @your-pm
/contracts/**  @your-pm
/CLAUDE.harness.md  @your-pm
